This paper deals with adversarial attacks in natural language processing, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also involves training a neural network to emulate the behavior of a white-box attack, which falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the vulnerability of a black-box API, which falls under the category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR) and "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV).
